ibmMvsTcpConnOutgoingPush.description: Sequence number of last pushed byte

ibmMvsTcpConnOutgoingUrg.name: ibmMvsTcpConnOutgoingUrg
ibmMvsTcpConnOutgoingUrg.description: Sequence number of last urg byte

ibmMvsTcpConnOutgoingWinSeq.name: ibmMvsTcpConnOutgoingWinSeq
ibmMvsTcpConnOutgoingWinSeq.description: Last sequence number in snd window

ibmMvsTcpConnSendWindowSeq.name: ibmMvsTcpConnSendWindowSeq
ibmMvsTcpConnSendWindowSeq.description: Last sequence number used, win update

ibmMvsTcpConnSendWindowAck.name: ibmMvsTcpConnSendWindowAck
ibmMvsTcpConnSendWindowAck.description: Last Ack number used, win update

ibmMvsTcpConnRcvNxt.name: ibmMvsTcpConnRcvNxt
ibmMvsTcpConnRcvNxt.description: Sequence number of next byte for TCP

ibmMvsTcpConnUsrRcvNxt.name: ibmMvsTcpConnUsrRcvNxt
ibmMvsTcpConnUsrRcvNxt.description: Sequence number of next byte for user

ibmMvsTcpConnIncomingPush.name: ibmMvsTcpConnIncomingPush
ibmMvsTcpConnIncomingPush.description: Sequence number of last pushed byte

ibmMvsTcpConnIncomingWinSeq.name: ibmMvsTcpConnIncomingWinSeq
ibmMvsTcpConnIncomingWinSeq.description: Last sequence number in receive window

ibmMvsTcpConnReXmt.name: ibmMvsTcpConnReXmt
ibmMvsTcpConnReXmt.description: Total number of retransmissions for this connection.

ibmMvsTcpConnReXmtCount.name: ibmMvsTcpConnReXmtCount
ibmMvsTcpConnReXmtCount.description: Number of times the current segment has been retransmitted.

ibmMvsTcpConnRoundTripTime.name: ibmMvsTcpConnRoundTripTime
ibmMvsTcpConnRoundTripTime.description: The amount of time that has elapsed, measured in milliseconds, from when the last TCP segment was transmitted by the TCP Stack until the ACK was received.

ibmMvsTcpConnSendMSS.name: ibmMvsTcpConnSendMSS
ibmMvsTcpConnSendMSS.description: Maximum Segment Size we can send

ibmMvsTcpConnResourceName.name: ibmMvsTcpConnResourceName
ibmMvsTcpConnResourceName.description: Resource Name is the text identification of this resource. It represents the user who opened the socket and is updated again during the bind processing.

ibmMvsTcpConnSubtask.name: ibmMvsTcpConnSubtask
ibmMvsTcpConnSubtask.description: The subtask ID represents the task that opened the socket and is updated again during bind processing. It is actually the TCB address.

ibmMvsTcpConnResourceId.name: ibmMvsTcpConnResourceId
ibmMvsTcpConnResourceId.description: Resource ID is the numeric identification of this resource.

ibmMvsTcpConnSockOpt.name: ibmMvsTcpConnSockOpt
ibmMvsTcpConnSockOpt.description: flag for socket options (1 byte hex value) -bit(1) = Sockets SO_REUSEADDR option -bit(2) = SO_OOBINLINE option -bit(3) = SO_LINGER option -bit(4) = T_MSGDONTROUTE -bit(5) = No delay (Nagle off) option -bit(6) = SO_Keepalive option -bit(7) = Currently timing linger -bit(8) = Currently timing keep alive

ibmMvsTcpConnTcpTimer.name: ibmMvsTcpConnTcpTimer
ibmMvsTcpConnTcpTimer.description: flag for TCP timers (1 byte hex value) -bit(1) = Currently timing round trip -bit(2) = Currently timing rexmt -bit(3) = Currently timing window probe -bit(4) = Dally timer currently set -bit(5) = Max Seg Lifetime timer set -bit(6) = T_ORDREL_IND is pending -bit(7) = Blocked for writing -bit(8) = Need to send a FIN

ibmMvsTcpConnTcpSig.name: ibmMvsTcpConnTcpSig
ibmMvsTcpConnTcpSig.description: 1 byte hex flag for TCP signals -bit(1) = Signal urgent data -bit(2) = Signal normal data -bit(3) = Signal timing finwait2 -bit(4) = <reserved> -bit(5) = <reserved> -bit(6) = Window scale option was received -bit(7) = Tcb on accept queue -bit(8) = Socket OPTMSS option

ibmMvsTcpConnTcpSel.name: ibmMvsTcpConnTcpSel
ibmMvsTcpConnTcpSel.description: TCP select flag byte for TCP select conditions. It is mapped as follows: -bit(1) = ON if active open, off passive -bit(2) = ON means timestamp option supported -bit(3) = ON when select for read issued -bit(4) = ON when select for write -bit(5) = ON when select for exception -bit(6) = ON means this is controlling -bit(7) = ON if accept in progress -bit(8) = ON means we are at OOB mark

ibmMvsTcpConnRttSeq.name: ibmMvsTcpConnRttSeq
ibmMvsTcpConnRttSeq.description: 4 byte value for the TCP sequence number

ibmMvsTcpConnBackoffCount.name: ibmMvsTcpConnBackoffCount
ibmMvsTcpConnBackoffCount.description: The value of this object will always be zero since it currently isn't reported.

ibmMvsTcpConnTcpDet.name: ibmMvsTcpConnTcpDet
ibmMvsTcpConnTcpDet.description: This flag will hold special TCP protocol conditions: - bit(1) = Delay Acks requested on PORT/PORTRANGE - bit(2) = Delay Acks requested on GATEWAY - bit(3) = Use default round trip parms - bit(4) = Connection is one hop away - bit(5) = Optimal max segment size request on PORT/PORTRANGE - bit(6) = FRCA conn deleted - bit(7) = PASCAL Multi Client - bit(8) = Load Balancing child

ibmMvsTcpConnTcpPol.name: ibmMvsTcpConnTcpPol
ibmMvsTcpConnTcpPol.description: This flag will indicates the following TCP poll conditions: - bit(1) = High priority data received - bit(2) = <reserved> - bit(3) = Written Normal - bit(4) = <reserved> - bit(5) = Reading Normal - bit(6) = <reserved> - bit(7) = <reserved> - bit(8) = <reserved>

ibmMvsTcpConnTargetAppl.name: ibmMvsTcpConnTargetAppl
ibmMvsTcpConnTargetAppl.description: When the corresponding TCP connection is for a 3172 Telnet session then this object contains the Target VTAM Application name.

ibmMvsTcpConnLuName.name: ibmMvsTcpConnLuName
ibmMvsTcpConnLuName.description: When the corresponding TCP connection is for a 3172 Telnet session then this object contains the VTAM LU name.

ibmMvsTcpConnClientUserId.name: ibmMvsTcpConnClientUserId
ibmMvsTcpConnClientUserId.description: When the corresponding TCP connection is for a 3172 Telnet session then this object contains the Client's userid.

ibmMvsTcpConnLogMode.name: ibmMvsTcpConnLogMode
ibmMvsTcpConnLogMode.description: When the corresponding TCP connection is for a 3172 Telnet session then this object contains the LOG Mode.

ibmMvsTcpConnProto.name: ibmMvsTcpConnProto
ibmMvsTcpConnProto.description: This flag will indicates the following Telnet modes: -bit(1 - 5) = <reserved> -bit(6) = TN3270 mode -bit(7) = TN3270E mode -bit(8) = line mode

ibmMvsTcpConnDupacks.name: ibmMvsTcpConnDupacks
ibmMvsTcpConnDupacks.description: Number of duplicate ACKs received for this connection.

ibmMvsTcpConnOptMaxSegmentSize.name: ibmMvsTcpConnOptMaxSegmentSize
ibmMvsTcpConnOptMaxSegmentSize.description: Optimal maximum segment size. The range of this value is from 0 to 65535.

ibmMvsTcpConnClusterConnFlag.name: ibmMvsTcpConnClusterConnFlag
ibmMvsTcpConnClusterConnFlag.description: This flag contains sysplex cluster connection types for this connection: -bit(1) = getsockopt(clusterconntype) requested -bit(2 - 4) = <reserved> -bit(5) = cluster internal -bit(6) = same image -bit(7) = same cluster -bit(8) = none

ibmMvsTcpConnInSegs.name: ibmMvsTcpConnInSegs
ibmMvsTcpConnInSegs.description: The number of segments received from IP for this connection.

ibmMvsTcpConnOutSegs.name: ibmMvsTcpConnOutSegs
ibmMvsTcpConnOutSegs.description: The number of segments sent to IP for this connection.

ibmMvsTcpConnDSField.name: ibmMvsTcpConnDSField
ibmMvsTcpConnDSField.description: The Differentiated Services field value in effect for this tcpConnTable entry. The value may be one of the following: - If there is a Service Policy Agent policy in effect for this entry, the value will be either: - The IPv4 TOS value defined by RFC 791 and 1349 - The Differentiated Services field value defined by RFC 2474 - If there is no Service Policy Agent policy in effect for this entry, the value will be 0.

ibmMvsTcpConnAcceptCount.name: ibmMvsTcpConnAcceptCount
ibmMvsTcpConnAcceptCount.description: The total number of connections accepted by this listener. Applies only to listener entries.

ibmMvsTcpConnExceedBacklog.name: ibmMvsTcpConnExceedBacklog
ibmMvsTcpConnExceedBacklog.description: The total number of connections dropped by this listener due to backlog exceeded. Applies only to listener entries.

ibmMvsTcpConnCurrBacklog.name: ibmMvsTcpConnCurrBacklog
ibmMvsTcpConnCurrBacklog.description: The current number of connections in backlog. Applies only to listener entries.

ibmMvsTcpConnMaxBacklog.name: ibmMvsTcpConnMaxBacklog
ibmMvsTcpConnMaxBacklog.description: The maximum number of connections allowed in backlog at one time. Applies only to listener entries.

ibmMvsTcpConnWindowScale.name: ibmMvsTcpConnWindowScale
ibmMvsTcpConnWindowScale.description: If true(1), the TCP window scale option is active for this connection. If false(2), the TCP window scale option is not active.

ibmMvsTcpConnTimeStamp.name: ibmMvsTcpConnTimeStamp
ibmMvsTcpConnTimeStamp.description: If true(1), the TCP timestamp option is active for this connection. If false(2), the TCP timestamp option is not active.

ibmMvsTcpConnServerResourceId.name: ibmMvsTcpConnServerResourceId
ibmMvsTcpConnServerResourceId.description: The numeric identification of the server (i.e. listener connection) associated with this client connection. This value only applies to load balancing servers which have bound to a port number for which SHAREPORT was specified on the PORT/PORTRANGE Profile statement. This value will be zero for client connections to servers which are not load balancing servers. The value of this object can be used to retrieve the listener entry from the ibmTcpipMvsTcpListenerTable.

ibmMvsTcpConnsClosed.name: ibmMvsTcpConnsClosed
ibmMvsTcpConnsClosed.description: Number of TCP connections that have corresponding sockets closed.

ibmMvsTcpPassiveDrops.name: ibmMvsTcpPassiveDrops
ibmMvsTcpPassiveDrops.description: Number of passive connection requests discarded.

ibmMvsTcpTimeWaitReused.name: ibmMvsTcpTimeWaitReused
ibmMvsTcpTimeWaitReused.description: Number of TCP connections in the TIMEWAIT state that have been reused for connections in the SYN-RCVD state.

ibmMvsTcpPredictAck.name: ibmMvsTcpPredictAck
ibmMvsTcpPredictAck.description: Number of inbound TCP acknowledgements with successful header prediction.

ibmMvsTcpPredictData.name: ibmMvsTcpPredictData
ibmMvsTcpPredictData.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments with successful header prediction.

ibmMvsTcpInDupAck.name: ibmMvsTcpInDupAck
ibmMvsTcpInDupAck.description: Number of inbound duplicate TCP acknowledgements.

ibmMvsTcpInBadSum.name: ibmMvsTcpInBadSum
ibmMvsTcpInBadSum.description: Number of inbound TCP segments discarded due to bad checksum.

ibmMvsTcpInBadLen.name: ibmMvsTcpInBadLen
ibmMvsTcpInBadLen.description: Number of inbound TCP segments discarded due to bad header len.

ibmMvsTcpInShort.name: ibmMvsTcpInShort
ibmMvsTcpInShort.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments discarded due to data length shorter than segment length.

ibmMvsTcpInPawsDrop.name: ibmMvsTcpInPawsDrop
ibmMvsTcpInPawsDrop.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments discarded due to old timestamp.

ibmMvsTcpInAllBeforeWin.name: ibmMvsTcpInAllBeforeWin
ibmMvsTcpInAllBeforeWin.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments with all data before current TCP window.

ibmMvsTcpInSomeBeforeWin.name: ibmMvsTcpInSomeBeforeWin
ibmMvsTcpInSomeBeforeWin.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments with some data before current TCP window.

ibmMvsTcpInAllAfterWin.name: ibmMvsTcpInAllAfterWin
ibmMvsTcpInAllAfterWin.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments with all data after current TCP window.

ibmMvsTcpInSomeAfterWin.name: ibmMvsTcpInSomeAfterWin
ibmMvsTcpInSomeAfterWin.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments with some data after current TCP window.

ibmMvsTcpInOutOfOrder.name: ibmMvsTcpInOutOfOrder
ibmMvsTcpInOutOfOrder.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments that did not contain the next expected sequence number (ie. out-of-order).

ibmMvsTcpInAfterClose.name: ibmMvsTcpInAfterClose
ibmMvsTcpInAfterClose.description: Number of inbound TCP data segments received after corresponding sockets have been closed.

ibmMvsTcpInWinProbes.name: ibmMvsTcpInWinProbes
ibmMvsTcpInWinProbes.description: Number of inbound TCP segments processed while current receive window size is zero.

ibmMvsTcpInWinUpdates.name: ibmMvsTcpInWinUpdates
ibmMvsTcpInWinUpdates.description: Number of inbound TCP segments that only change receive window size.

ibmMvsTcpOutWinUpdates.name: ibmMvsTcpOutWinUpdates
ibmMvsTcpOutWinUpdates.description: Number of outbound TCP segments that only change receive window size.

ibmMvsTcpOutDelayAcks.name: ibmMvsTcpOutDelayAcks
ibmMvsTcpOutDelayAcks.description: Number of delayed outbound TCP acknowledgements.

ibmMvsTcpOutWinProbes.name: ibmMvsTcpOutWinProbes
ibmMvsTcpOutWinProbes.description: Number of outbound window probe requests.

ibmMvsTcpRxmtTimers.name: ibmMvsTcpRxmtTimers
ibmMvsTcpRxmtTimers.description: Number of TCP retransmit timer pops.

ibmMvsTcpRxmtDrops.name: ibmMvsTcpRxmtDrops
ibmMvsTcpRxmtDrops.description: Number of TCP connections dropped due to retransmit threshold exceeded.

ibmMvsTcpPMTURxmts.name: ibmMvsTcpPMTURxmts
ibmMvsTcpPMTURxmts.description: Number of outbound TCP segments retransmitted due to path MTU discovery.

ibmMvsTcpPMTUErrors.name: ibmMvsTcpPMTUErrors
ibmMvsTcpPMTUErrors.description: Number of TCP connections that exceeded path MTU discovery retransmit threshold.

ibmMvsTcpProbeDrops.name: ibmMvsTcpProbeDrops
ibmMvsTcpProbeDrops.description: Number of TCP connections dropped due to no response while sending window probe requests.

ibmMvsTcpKeepAliveDrops.name: ibmMvsTcpKeepAliveDrops
ibmMvsTcpKeepAliveDrops.description: Number of TCP connections dropped due to no response while sending keepalive probe requests.

ibmMvsTcpFinwait2Drops.name: ibmMvsTcpFinwait2Drops
ibmMvsTcpFinwait2Drops.description: Number of TCP connections dropped due to FINWAIT2 timer expiring prior to receiving FIN segment.

ibmTcpipMvsTcpListenerTable.name: ibmTcpipMvsTcpListenerTable
ibmTcpipMvsTcpListenerTable.description: Provides TCP connection information for connections in Listen state. Connections in this state are assumed to be servers so only server MIB objects are supported.

ibmTcpipMvsTcpListenerEntry.name: ibmTcpipMvsTcpListenerEntry
ibmTcpipMvsTcpListenerEntry.description: Descibes a particular tcp listener entry.

ibmMvsTcpListenerResourceId.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerResourceId
ibmMvsTcpListenerResourceId.description: Resource ID is the numeric identification of this resource. This value is also known as the connection ID.

ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalAddrType.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalAddrType
ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalAddrType.description: The IP address type of the ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalAddr object.

ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalAddr.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalAddr
ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalAddr.description: The local IP address for this TCP connection. In the case of a connection in the listen state which is willing to accept connections for any IP interface associated with the node, the value 0.0.0.0 is used.

ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalPort.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalPort
ibmMvsTcpListenerLocalPort.description: The local port number for this TCP connection.

ibmMvsTcpListenerRemoteAddrType.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerRemoteAddrType
ibmMvsTcpListenerRemoteAddrType.description: The IP address type of the ibmMvsTcpListenerRemoteAddr object.

ibmMvsTcpListenerRemoteAddr.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerRemoteAddr
ibmMvsTcpListenerRemoteAddr.description: The remote ip address for this TCP connection.

ibmMvsTcpListenerRemotePort.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerRemotePort
ibmMvsTcpListenerRemotePort.description: The remote port number for this TCP connection.

ibmMvsTcpListenerAcceptCount.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerAcceptCount
ibmMvsTcpListenerAcceptCount.description: The total number of connections accepted by this listener.

ibmMvsTcpListenerExceedBacklog.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerExceedBacklog
ibmMvsTcpListenerExceedBacklog.description: The total number of connections dropped by this listener due to backlog exceeded.

ibmMvsTcpListenerCurrBacklog.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerCurrBacklog
ibmMvsTcpListenerCurrBacklog.description: The current number of connections in backlog.

ibmMvsTcpListenerMaxBacklog.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerMaxBacklog
ibmMvsTcpListenerMaxBacklog.description: The maximum number of connections allowed in backlog at one time.

ibmMvsTcpListenerResourceName.name: ibmMvsTcpListenerResourceName
ibmMvsTcpListenerResourceName.description: Resource Name is the text identification of this resource. It represents the user who opened the socket and is updated again during the bind processing.

ibmTcpipMvsUdpTable.name: ibmTcpipMvsUdpTable
ibmTcpipMvsUdpTable.description: Extends udp table to support additional UDP listener information.

ibmMvsUdpLastAct.name: ibmMvsUdpLastAct
ibmMvsUdpLastAct.description: The amount of time that has elapsed since the corresponding entry has had any activity. Measured in hundreds of seconds.

ibmMvsUdpTos.name: ibmMvsUdpTos
ibmMvsUdpTos.description: The type of service in effect for this entry. Currently, not supported and will return a zero when retrieved.

ibmMvsUdpResourceName.name: ibmMvsUdpResourceName
ibmMvsUdpResourceName.description: Resource Name is the text identification of this resource. It represents the ?itName value of the associating resource's relationship with the UDP Stack.

ibmMvsUdpResourceId.name: ibmMvsUdpResourceId
ibmMvsUdpResourceId.description: Resource ID is the numeric identification of this resource.

ibmMvsUdpSockOpt.name: ibmMvsUdpSockOpt
ibmMvsUdpSockOpt.description: flag for socket options (1 byte hex valuel) -bit(1) = allow broadcast address -bit(2) = allow loopback of datagrams -bit(3) = bypass normal routing -bit(4) = forward ICMP message (Pascal) -bit(5) = outgoing multicast datagrams -bit(6) = incoming multicast datagrams -bit(7) = <reserved> -bit(8) = <reserved>

ibmMvsUdpEntryState.name: ibmMvsUdpEntryState
ibmMvsUdpEntryState.description: A entry's state will always be active unless it is to be deleted. This is accomplished by setting this object to delete. A set of active is invalid.

ibmMvsUdpMcastTTL.name: ibmMvsUdpMcastTTL
ibmMvsUdpMcastTTL.description: Time-to-live value for a multicast datagram.

ibmMvsUdpMcastLoopback.name: ibmMvsUdpMcastLoopback
ibmMvsUdpMcastLoopback.description: If true(1), indicates that loopback is enabled for outbound multicast datagrams. If false(2), indicates either that loopback is disabled for outbound multicast datagrams or that the socket is not processing outgoing multicast datagrams. The value of object ibmMvsUdpSockOpt will indicate whether or not the socket is processing outgoing multicast datagrams.

ibmMvsUdpMcastLinkAddr.name: ibmMvsUdpMcastLinkAddr
ibmMvsUdpMcastLinkAddr.description: IP address of the interface used for outbound multicast datagrams.

ibmMvsUdpDSField.name: ibmMvsUdpDSField
ibmMvsUdpDSField.description: The Differentiated Services field value in effect for this udpTable entry. The value may be one of the following: - If there is a Service Policy Agent policy in effect for this entry, the value will be either: - The IPv4 TOS value defined by RFC 791 and 1349 - The Differentiated Services field value defined by RFC 2474 - If there is no Service Policy Agent policy in effect for this entry, but the entry is being used for an Enterprise Extender connection, the value will be one of the following VTAM IP Type of Service values in hexadecimal. See the SNA Network Implementation Guide for a descripton of VTAM IP Type of Service): 20 - Low 40 - Medium 80 - High C0 - Network - If neither of the above are true, then this value will be 0.

ibmTcpipMvsUdpMcastRecvTable.name: ibmTcpipMvsUdpMcastRecvTable
ibmTcpipMvsUdpMcastRecvTable.description: The table listing UDP sockets that receive multicast data. The table is ordered by the interface being used by the socket for incoming datagrams, the UDP socket (local IP address and port), and the mulitcast group to which the socket is registerd.

ibmTcpipMvsUdpMcastRecvEntry.name: ibmTcpipMvsUdpMcastRecvEntry
ibmTcpipMvsUdpMcastRecvEntry.description: Entry defining a UDP socket that receives multicast data.

ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLocalAddress.name: ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLocalAddress
ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLocalAddress.description: The local IP address for this UDP listener. In the case of a UDP listener which is willing to accept datagrams for any IP interface associated with the node, the value 0.0.0.0 is used.

ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLocalPort.name: ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLocalPort
ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLocalPort.description: The local port number for this UDP listener.

ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvGroup.name: ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvGroup
ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvGroup.description: Specifies the IP address of the multicast group

ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLinkAddr.name: ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLinkAddr
ibmMvsUdpMcastRecvLinkAddr.description: The IP address of the interface used for incoming packets for this multicast group on this socket.

ibmMvsIpInDevLayerCalls.name: ibmMvsIpInDevLayerCalls
ibmMvsIpInDevLayerCalls.description: Number of times the inbound TCP/IP Data Path has received control from the Device Layer. This counter may be less than the number of packets received (ipInReceives), as a single inbound call may process several inbound packets.

ibmMvsIpInUnpackErrors.name: ibmMvsIpInUnpackErrors
ibmMvsIpInUnpackErrors.description: Number of times a received frame could not be unpacked into its consistuent datagrams, resulting in packet loss. A non-zero value in this counter may be evidence of a buffer-formatting problem within a device.

ibmMvsIpInDiscardsMemory.name: ibmMvsIpInDiscardsMemory
ibmMvsIpInDiscardsMemory.description: Number of inbound packets discarded due to a CSM storage shortage.

ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsDlcSynch.name: ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsDlcSynch
ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsDlcSynch.description: Number of outbound packets discarded due to a synchronous error in the Data Link Control. Synchronous DLC errors are detected on the interface between TCP/IP and VTAM, and are typically not related to channel or device errors.

ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsDlcAsynch.name: ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsDlcAsynch
ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsDlcAsynch.description: Number of outbound packets discarded due to an asynchronous error in the Data Link Control. Asynchronous DLC errors may occur for a variety of reasons, including channel/device errors, incorrectly formatted data, or storage shortage within VTAM.

ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsMemory.name: ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsMemory
ibmMvsIpOutDiscardsMemory.description: Number of outbound packets discarded due to a CSM storage shortage.

osaexpChannelTable.name: osaexpChannelTable
osaexpChannelTable.description: One entry in this table will exist per OSA-Express Device Interface. If the values for objects ibmMvsOsaExpCurLparName/Num are not the same as the values for objects ibmMvsOsaExpManLparName/Num then the OSA/SF running in the current LPAR is not the managing OSA/SF for this Device. The utilization object values will be reset when the CHPID is reset. The processor utilization objects are the sum of the per LPAR processor utilization values in the corresponding osaexpPerfTable entries for the adapter.

osaexpChannelEntry.name: osaexpChannelEntry
osaexpChannelEntry.description: Definition of a single entry in the osaexpChannelTable. Indexed by the ifIndex of the corresponding DEVICE interface.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelNumber.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelNumber
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelNumber.description: The channel number for this interface.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelType.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelType
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelType.description: For OSA-Express adapters supporting QDIO mode, the value will be osd(17). For OSA-Express adapters supporting non-QDIO mode, the value will be ose(16).

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelSubType.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelSubType
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelSubType.description: Indicates how the channel is configured.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelMode.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelMode
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelMode.description: Configured mode of the OSA-Express adapter. This value will be set to nothingConfigured(1) for QDIO adapters that are not configured for LAN Emulation.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelState.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelState
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelState.description: Hardware channel state: online, not installed, or offline.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelShared.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelShared
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelShared.description: An OSA-Express Channel can be shared across multiple LPARs. This object indicates if this channel is currently being shared.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelNumPorts.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelNumPorts
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelNumPorts.description: Number of ports on the OSA-Express adapter. For non-ATM adapters, the value reflects the number of physical ports. For ATM adapters the value reflects the number of logical ports. For ATM155 Native mode adapters, the value should be 1. For ATM155 QDIO LAN Emulation mode adapters, the value can be 1 or 2 depending on the number of logical ports configured.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelDeterNodeDesc.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelDeterNodeDesc
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelDeterNodeDesc.description: Describes the generic node descriptor layout. This object represents the ND obtained from the CHSC instruction: /* ND Flags */ int bValidity :3; /* 1:is ND valid */ int bNodeType :1; /* 1:0=dev,1=chnlsubstm nod*/ int bInternal :1; /* internal(1)/external(0) */ int bCHPinvalid :1; /* IF =1,NDCHPID is invalid*/ int bNDRsvd1 :2; /* spare bits for alignment*/ char NDType; /* reserved by architecture*/ char NDClass; /* Class for subsystem node*/ char NDCHPID; /* CHP ID for specified int*/ char NDTypeNum 6 ; /* type number of the SDC */ char NDModelNum 3 ; /* ND model number in the form of 3 EBCDIC OCTETS */ char NDMfgr 3 ; /* ND manufacturer in the form of 3 EBCDIC OCTETS */ char NDMfgrPlant 2 ; /* ND plant of manufacture (2 EBCDIC OCTETS) */ char NDSeqNum 12 ; /* ND sequence number (12 EBCDIC OCTETS) */ char NDTag 2 ; /* ND tag */

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelControlUnitNumber.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelControlUnitNumber
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelControlUnitNumber.description: The control unit number associated with the OSA-Express Channel.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCodeLevel.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCodeLevel
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCodeLevel.description: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCodeLevel is the firmware (or micro code level) of the OSA adapter. For example, OSA adapter level 05.60 would be represented as 0x0560 by this object.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCurLparName.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCurLparName
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCurLparName.description: LPAR name of the OSA/SF from which this data was retrieved.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCurLparNum.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCurLparNum
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelCurLparNum.description: LPAR number of the OSA/SF from which this data was retrieved.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelManLparName.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelManLparName
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelManLparName.description: LPAR name of the OSA Support Facility managing this channel. Only one OSA/SF can manage a OSA-Express Channel within an MVS Sysplex even though multiple OSA/SFs can retrieve information from the same OSA-Express Channel.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelManLparNum.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelManLparNum
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelManLparNum.description: LPAR number of the OSA Support Facility managing this channel (set to 0xFFFF if not being managed by a OSA/SF).

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtil1Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtil1Min
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtil1Min.description: The average, over a 1 minute interval, of the percentage of time that the PCI bus was utilized to transfer data. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtil1Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtil1Min
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtil1Min.description: The average, over a 1 minute interval, of the percentage of time that the CHPID Processor was utilized to transfer data. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtil5Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtil5Min
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtil5Min.description: The average, over a 5 minute interval, of the percentage of time that the PCI bus was utilized to transfer data. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtil5Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtil5Min
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtil5Min.description: The average, over a 5 minute interval, of the percentage of time that the CHPID Processor was utilized to transfer data. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtilHour.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtilHour
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelPCIBusUtilHour.description: The average, over an hour interval, of the percentage of time that the PCI bus was utilized to transfer data. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtilHour.name: ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtilHour
ibmMvsOsaExpChannelProcessorUtilHour.description: The average, over an hour interval, of the percentage of time that the CHPID Processor was utilized to transfer data. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

osaexpPerfTable.name: osaexpPerfTable
osaexpPerfTable.description: This table provides performance information per each LPAR's utilization of an OSA-Express adapter. The values will be reset when the adapter CHPID is reset.

osaexpPerfEntry.name: osaexpPerfEntry
osaexpPerfEntry.description: Definition of a single entry in the osaexpPerfTable. Indexed by the ifIndex of the corresponding DEVICE interface and the LPAR number.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfLparNum.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfLparNum
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfLparNum.description: LPAR number of the LPAR to which the performance objects apply.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil1Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil1Min
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil1Min.description: The average, over a 1 minute interval, of the percentage of time that the CHPID Processor was utilized to transfer data for a specific LPAR. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRate1Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRate1Min
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRate1Min.description: The average, over a 1 minute interval, of the number of inbound kilobytes processed for a specific LPAR. When the ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil1Min object for a specific LPAR has a value of -1, then the interval data could not be retrieved from the adapter and this object will have a value of zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRate1Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRate1Min
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRate1Min.description: The average, over a 1 minute interval, of the number of outbound kilobytes processed for a specific LPAR. When the ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil1Min object for a specific LPAR has a value of -1, then the interval data could not be retrieved from the adapter and this object will have a value of zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil5Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil5Min
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil5Min.description: The average, over a 5 minute interval, of the percentage of time that the CHPID Processor was utilized to transfer data for a specific LPAR. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRate5Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRate5Min
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRate5Min.description: The average, over a 5 minute interval, of the number of inbound kilobytes processed for a specific LPAR. When the ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil5Min object for a specific LPAR has a value of -1, then the interval data could not be retrieved from the adapter and this object will have a value of zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRate5Min.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRate5Min
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRate5Min.description: The average, over a 5 minute interval, of the number of outbound kilobytes processed for a specific LPAR. When the ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtil5Min object for a specific LPAR has a value of -1, then the interval data could not be retrieved from the adapter and this object will have a value of zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtilHour.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtilHour
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtilHour.description: The average, over an hour interval, of the percentage of time that the CHPID Processor was utilized to transfer data for a specific LPAR. It does not include idle time or time used by routine maintenance tasks. The range of valid values for this object is 0 to 100%. A value of -1 indicates that the value could not be retrieved from the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRateHour.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRateHour
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfInKbytesRateHour.description: The average, over an hour interval, of the number of inbound kilobytes processed for a specific LPAR. When the ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtilHour object for a specific LPAR has a value of -1, then the interval data could not be retrieved from the adapter and this object will have a value of zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRateHour.name: ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRateHour
ibmMvsOsaExpPerfOutKbytesRateHour.description: The average, over an hour interval, of the number of outbound kilobytes processed for a specific LPAR. When the ibmMvsOsaExpPerfProcessorUtilHour object for a specific LPAR has a value of -1, then the interval data could not be retrieved from the adapter and this object will have a value of zero.

osaexpEthPortTable.name: osaexpEthPortTable
osaexpEthPortTable.description: This table is intended to represent the ethernet Ports associated with the osaexpChannelTable entries for ethernet adapters. Each OSA-Express Channel has one or more Ports.

osaexpEthPortEntry.name: osaexpEthPortEntry
osaexpEthPortEntry.description: Definition of a single entry in the osaexpEthPortTable. Indexed by the ifIndex of the corresponding LINK interface.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortHardwareState.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortHardwareState
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortHardwareState.description: The hardware state of the port: 1 - Unknown port hardware state. 2 - OSA has detected a loss of signal on the link. (A likely cause of this condition is an improperly installed or missing cable connection on the port). For OSA-Express ATM, this condition can also be caused by registration failure. 3 - Port is disabled. The reason for the port being disabled is set in object ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortDisabledStatus. 4 - Port is enabled.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortDisabledStatus.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortDisabledStatus
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortDisabledStatus.description: When the value of ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortHardwareState is disabled(3), this object explains the reason for the disabled state. The value for this object may be a combination of the following: 0x0001 Disabled internal port failure 0x0002 Disabled service processor request 0x0004 Disabled network request 0x0008 Disabled OSA/SF request 0x0010 Disabled configuration change 0x0020 Disabled link failure threshold exceeded 0x0040 Disabled port temporarily disabled When the value of ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortHardwareState is not disabled(3), the value of this object will be zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortConfigSpeed.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortConfigSpeed
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortConfigSpeed.description: The configured port speed. For OSA-Express Gigabit Ethernet adapters the port speed can not be configured so the value of this object will be 1000MbFullDuplex(7).

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortMacAddrActive.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortMacAddrActive
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortMacAddrActive.description: A 6 byte OCTET STRING which contains the current MAC address in use on the adapter.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortMacAddrBurntIn.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortMacAddrBurntIn
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortMacAddrBurntIn.description: A 6 byte OCTET STRING which contains the adapter's burned in MAC address.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortOutPackets.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortOutPackets
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortOutPackets.description: The count of the total number of packets transmitted from this port. A CHPID reset will cause this value to be reset to zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInPackets.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInPackets
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInPackets.description: The count of the total number of packets received by this port. A CHPID reset will cause this value to be reset to zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInGroupFrames.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInGroupFrames
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInGroupFrames.description: The count of the total number of group frames received by this port. A CHPID reset will cause this value to be reset to zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInBroadcastFrames.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInBroadcastFrames
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInBroadcastFrames.description: The count of the total number of broadcast frames received by this port. A CHPID reset will cause this value to be reset to zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortName.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortName
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortName.description: Specifies the Port Name which must also be entered at the connection manager on the host and the application. Port Name is specifed to OSA/SF as a config file parameter (PCM_NAME). This value is also specified via ILMI as the value of the atmfPortMyIfName object. Does not apply to an ATM OSA-2 adapter configured for ATM IP Forwarding mode, or an OSA-Express ATM155 adapter configured for QDIO LAN Emulation mode.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInUnknownIPFrames.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInUnknownIPFrames
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortInUnknownIPFrames.description: The count of the total number of packets that were discarded because they did not have a matching IP address and there was no primary nor secondary router default defined. This object is not supported for Fast Ethernet adapters so the value will be zero.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortGroupMacAddrs.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortGroupMacAddrs
ibmMvsOsaExpEthPortGroupMacAddrs.description: This field contains the active Group Addresses. An individual Group Address is 6 bytes long. Therefore, this field is actually 32 times (OCTET STRING(SIZE(6)) + 2 bytes of padding) long.

osaexpEthSnaTable.name: osaexpEthSnaTable
osaexpEthSnaTable.description: This table is intended to represent the data that is available from an OSA-Express ethernet Port that is running in SNA mode. An entry in this table is associated with the osaexpEthPortTable entries.

osaexpEthSnaEntry.name: osaexpEthSnaEntry
osaexpEthSnaEntry.description: Definition of a single entry in the osaexpEthSnaTable. Indexed by the ifIndex of the corresponding LINK interface.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaInactTimer.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaInactTimer
ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaInactTimer.description: The inactivity timer. An enabled inactivity timer (Ti) periodically tests the viability of the network media. The timer setting applies to all the clients on the target LAN, not to individual clients. The timer interval indicates how quickly a failure of the network media can be detected when the connection is quiescent. If the Ti timer times out, a supervisory poll frame is sent over the connection. The T1 response, or reply, timer clocks the supervisory poll. If the T1 timer times out, the supervisory poll is retransmitted. OSA can retransmit a supervisory poll up to 8 times. If no response is received after the last retransmission, the link is declared inoperative, and the MVS program issues a message. The value will either be zero, or in the range of 24 to 9000 in units of 100th of a second.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaRespTimer.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaRespTimer
ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaRespTimer.description: The response timer. The T1 timer clocks link events that require responses from clients on the network. These link events include SABME/UA exchanges, I-frame link protocol data unit (LPDU) transmissions, and supervisory polls. The value is expressed as an integer in units of 10th of a second.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaAckTimer.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaAckTimer
ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaAckTimer.description: The acknowledgement timer. An OSA starts the T2 timer when it receives an I-format LPDU and stops when it sends an acknowledgement. An acknowledgement is sent either when an outgoing I frame is sent, which acts as the acknowledgement, or when N3 number of I-format LPDUs has been received. If the T2 timer times out, the OSA must send an acknowledgement. The value is expressed as an integer in units of 100th of a second.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaMaxIFramesBeforeAck.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaMaxIFramesBeforeAck
ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaMaxIFramesBeforeAck.description: Maximum I frames before ACK (N3). The maximum number of I-format link protocol data units (LPDUs) that can be received by an OSA before it sends an acknowledgement (N3 count). It is also called the receive window count.

ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaMaxTransmitWindow.name: ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaMaxTransmitWindow
ibmMvsOsaExpEthSnaMaxTransmitWindow.description: SNA maximum transmit window (TW). The maximum number of outstanding I-format link protocol data units (LPDUs). It is also called the maximum transmit window count or the maximum window out count. The TW count allows the sender to transmit frames before that sender is forced to halt and wait for an acknowledgement. Therefore, the receiver should be able to absorb that number of frames, either in its service access point (SAP) buffers or within the buffers in workstation memory.

ibmMvsDVIPATable.name: ibmMvsDVIPATable
ibmMvsDVIPATable.description: Each entry in this table represents a Dynamic VIPA (DVIPA) interface configured to this stack, and supports DVIPA status information.

ibmMvsDVIPAEntry.name: ibmMvsDVIPAEntry
ibmMvsDVIPAEntry.description: Definition of a single entry in the ibmMvsDVIPATable.

ibmMvsDVIPAIpAddrType.name: ibmMvsDVIPAIpAddrType
ibmMvsDVIPAIpAddrType.description: The IP address type of the ibmMvsDVIPAIpAddr object.

ibmMvsDVIPAMaskType.name: ibmMvsDVIPAMaskType
ibmMvsDVIPAMaskType.description: The IP address type of the ibmMvsDVIPAMaskAddr object This object will be set to unknown(0) for entries whose ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin value is backup(2).

ibmMvsDVIPAMaskAddr.name: ibmMvsDVIPAMaskAddr
ibmMvsDVIPAMaskAddr.description: The address mask. This object will be set to a zero-length string for entries whose ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin value is backup(2).

ibmMvsDVIPAStatus.name: ibmMvsDVIPAStatus
ibmMvsDVIPAStatus.description: The status of this DVIPA on the stack. A status of unknown(1) should not occur and represents an error.

ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin.name: ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin
ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin.description: The origin of how this DVIPA came to be configured to the stack. A value of backup(2) or define(3) indicates which VIPADYNAMIC Profile statement was used to configure the DVIPA to the stack. A value of rangeBind(4) indicates that the DVIPA was dynamically defined when an application issued a BIND function call. A value of rangeIoctl(5) indicates that the DVIPA was dynamically defined when an application issued the SIOCSVIPA IOCTL function call. A value of target(6) indicates that the DVIPA was dynamically defined on the stack because this stack is a target stack for the Sysplex Distributor function. A status of unknown(1) should not occur and represents an error.

ibmMvsDVIPARank.name: ibmMvsDVIPARank
ibmMvsDVIPARank.description: This stack's rank in the chain of backup stacks for a given dynamic VIPA. For entries whose ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin value is not backup(2) or define(3), this object does not apply and will be set to -1.

ibmMvsDVIPADistributeStatus.name: ibmMvsDVIPADistributeStatus
ibmMvsDVIPADistributeStatus.description: The status of this DVIPA on the stack in relation to the Sysplex Distributor function. A value of none(1) indicates that the DVIPA is not participating in the Sysplex Distributor function. A value of distributor(2) indicates that the stack is a distributor for this DVIPA. A value of target(3) indicates that the stack is a target stack for this DVIPA. A value of distributorAndTarget(4) indicates that the stack is both a distributor and a target stack for this DVIPA.

ibmMvsDVIPAMoveable.name: ibmMvsDVIPAMoveable
ibmMvsDVIPAMoveable.description: The manner in which a dynamic VIPA IP address should be moved to another stack. A value of none(1) indicates that moveable status does not apply to this DVIPA. This value would be set for entries where backup is set as the value for the ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin and ibmMvsDVIPAStatus objects. For DVIPA IP addresses activated as the result of a VIPADEFINE configuration statement, a value of immediate(2) means that this dynamic VIPA can be moved to another stack as soon as the other stack requests ownership of the DVIPA by executing a VIPADEFINE for the same dynamic VIPA. Any existing connections on this stack will be maintained by the new owning stack until the connections are closed. All new connection requests will be directed to the new owning stack. A value of whenIdle(3) means that this dynamic VIPA can be moved to another stack when there are no connections for this dynamic VIPA on this stack. While there are existing connections, any new connection requests will continue to be directed to this stack. For DVIPA IP addresses activated as the result of a VIPARANGE configuration and a subsequent SIOCSVIPA IOCTL or BIND, a value of nonDisruptive(4) means that this DVIPA can be moved to another stack as soon as the other stack requests ownership of the DVIPA by creating the same DVIPA via a subsequent BIND or SIOCSVIPA IOCTL. Any existing connections on this stack will be maintained by the new owning stack until the connections are closed. All new connection requests will be directed to the new stack. A value of disruptive(5) means that one of two different behaviors will occur: - In the case of a subsequent BIND by an application on another stack, no movement of the DVIPA will occur the second application will presumably be disrupted because the BIND fails. (The first application is unaware that another BIND occurred.) - In the case of a subsequent SIOCSVIPA IOCTL, the DVIPA will move to another stack but connections to the DVIPA on this stack will be broken.

ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrEnabled.name: ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrEnabled
ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrEnabled.description: The status of this DVIPA on the stack in relation to the Service Manager function. A value of true(1) indicates that the DVIPA is participating in the Service Manager function. A value of false(2) indicates that the DVIPA is not participating in the Service Manager function.

ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfTable.name: ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfTable
ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfTable.description: Each entry in this table represents a subnet defined by the VIPARANGE Profile statement in which requests for activating a DVIPA via a BIND or SIOCSVIPA IOCTL, will be honored.

ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfEntry.name: ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfEntry
ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfEntry.description: Definition of a single entry in the ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfTable.

ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfIpAddrType.name: ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfIpAddrType
ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfIpAddrType.description: The IP address type of the ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfIpAddr object.

ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfMaskType.name: ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfMaskType
ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfMaskType.description: The IP address type of the ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfMaskAddr object.

ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfMoveable.name: ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfMoveable
ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfMoveable.description: The manner in which a dynamic VIPA IP address defined by a VIPARANGE statement, should be moved to another stack. A value of nonDisruptive(1) means that this DVIPA can be moved to another stack as soon as the other stack requests ownership of the DVIPA by creating the same DVIPA via a subsequent BIND or SIOCSVIPA IOCTL. Any existing connections on this stack will be maintained by the new owning stack until the connections are closed. All new connection requests will be directed to the new stack. A value of disruptive(2) means that one of two different behaviors will occur: - In the case of a subsequent BIND by an application on another stack, no movement of the DVIPA will occur the second application will presumably be disrupted because the BIND fails. (The first application is unaware that another BIND occurred.) - In the case of a subsequent SIOCSVIPA IOCTL, the DVIPA will move to another stack but connections to the DVIPA on this stack will be broken.

ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfStatus.name: ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfStatus
ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfTable. Note that an attempt to set any read-create object defined within an ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfEntry while the value of ibmMvsDVIPARangeConfStatus is active(1) should result in an inconsistentValue error.

ibmMvsDVIPADistConfTable.name: ibmMvsDVIPADistConfTable
ibmMvsDVIPADistConfTable.description: Each entry in this table represents a dynamic VIPA and port for which connection requests are to be distributed to other stacks as defined by the VIPADISTRIBUTE Profile statement.

ibmMvsDVIPAConnRoutingTable.name: ibmMvsDVIPAConnRoutingTable
ibmMvsDVIPAConnRoutingTable.description: Each entry in this table represents a dynamic VIPA TCP connection. Entries will be supported in the table for all dynamic VIPA interfaces for which MOVEABLE IMMEDIATE or NONDISRUPTIVE was specified. On a Sysplex Distributor routing stack, there will be an entry in this table for every connection being routed through the distributor. On a stack taking over a dynamic VIPA, there will be an entry in this table for every connection to the dynamic VIPA. On a Sysplex Distributor target stack or a stack which is in the process of giving up a dynamic VIPA, there will be an entry in this table for every connection for which the stack is an endpoint.

This table is not supported by stacks which are only targets of the Sysplex Distributor function.

ibmMvsDVIPADistPortWlmWeight.name: ibmMvsDVIPADistPortWlmWeight
ibmMvsDVIPADistPortWlmWeight.description: The Workload Manager weight value for the MVS system on which the target stack is located. The value is normalized such that the lowest value is 1. This weight value is an indication of the MVS system's available CPU capacity. The lower the value the lower the capacity.

ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrMulticastIpAddrType.name: ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrMulticastIpAddrType
ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrMulticastIpAddrType.description: The IP address type of the ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrMulticastIpAddr object.

ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrMulticastIpAddr.name: ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrMulticastIpAddr
ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrMulticastIpAddr.description: The type of multicast IP address that will be used for communications between the Sysplex Distributor and the routers acting as Forwarding Agents. This object reflects values from the VIPASMPARMS Profile statement for the Sysplex Distributor Service Manager function.

ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrPort.name: ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrPort
ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrPort.description: The type of multicast IP address that will be used for communications between the Sysplex Distributor and the routers acting as Forwarding Agents. This object reflects values from the VIPASMPARMS Profile statement for the Sysplex Distributor Service Manager function.

ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrPasswordSpecified.name: ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrPasswordSpecified
ibmMvsDVIPAServMgrPasswordSpecified.description: Indicates whether a password value was specified on the VIPASMPARMS Profile statement for the Sysplex Distributor Service Manager function. A value of true(1) indicates that a password was specified. A value of false(2) indicates that a password was not specified. The password enables MD5 encryption for all communications between the Sysplex Distributor function and routers acting as Forwarding Agents. This password must match configured on the Forwarding Agents.

ibmMvsDVIPATrapControl.name: ibmMvsDVIPATrapControl
ibmMvsDVIPATrapControl.description: The value of this object determines which traps will be generated for all dynamic VIPA events. The value of this object is initialized to dvipaStatusChange(0) and dvipaRemoved(1) so that only those traps will be automatically generated. The following values are only applicable to Sysplex Distributor distributing stacks: - targetAdded(2) - targetRemoved(3) - targetServerStarted(4) - targetServerEnded(5) The following traps are generated when the corresponding bit value for this object is set: BIT value Trap --================================== dvipaStatusChange(0) ibmMvsDVIPAStatusChange dvipaRemoved(1) ibmMvsDVIPARemoved targetAdded(2) ibmMvsDVIPATargetAdded targetRemoved(3) ibmMvsDVIPATargetRemoved targetServerStarted(4 ) ibmMvsDVIPATargetServerStarted targetServerEnded(5) ibmMvsDVIPATargetServerEnded

ibmMvsAtmOsasfAtmPvcCreate.name: ibmMvsAtmOsasfAtmPvcCreate
ibmMvsAtmOsasfAtmPvcCreate.description: This trap is generated when OSA/SF sends a asynch notification to the TCP/IP DPI Subagent that a PVC was created for a given OSA Port. This notification contains the corresponding ibmMvsAtmOsasfPortName instance. Representation of this will contain the aal5 layer interface ifIndex of the port, the PVC name len, and the PVC name in ASCII as 'ifIndex.pvcNameOctetCount.pvcNameInASCIINvt'.

ibmMvsAtmOsasfAtmPvcDelete.name: ibmMvsAtmOsasfAtmPvcDelete
ibmMvsAtmOsasfAtmPvcDelete.description: This trap is generated when OSA/SF sends a asyn notification to the TCP/IP DPI Subagent that a PVC was deleted for a given OSA Port. This notification contains the corresponding ibmMvsAtmOsasfPortName instance. Representation of this will contain the aal5 layer interface ifIndex of the port, the PVC name len, and the PVC name in ASCII as 'ifIndex.pvcNameOctetCount.pvcNameInASCIINvt'.

ibmMvsDVIPAStatusChange.name: ibmMvsDVIPAStatusChange
ibmMvsDVIPAStatusChange.description: This trap is generated when a dynamic VIPA is defined or its status changes on a TCP/IP stack. The ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin value indicates the reason why the DVIPA was originally defined. The instance value for the trap objects will contain the affected DVIPA IP address.

ibmMvsDVIPARemoved.name: ibmMvsDVIPARemoved
ibmMvsDVIPARemoved.description: This trap is generated when a dynamic VIPA is removed from a TCP/Id stack. The ibmMvsDVIPAOrigin value indicates the reason why the DVIPA was previously defined. The ibmMvsDVIPAStatus object reflects the status before DVIPA was removed. The instance value for the trap objects will contain the affected DVIPA IP address.

ibmMvsDVIPATargetAdded.name: ibmMvsDVIPATargetAdded
ibmMvsDVIPATargetAdded.description: This trap is generated by a Sysplex Distributor stack when it determines that a designated target stack is active. Stacks are designated as target stacks on the VIPADISTRIBUTE Profile statement. The instance value for the ibmMvsDVIPADistConfStatus object will indicate the affected DVIPA IP address, the distributed port, and the target stack's dynamic XCF IP address.

ibmMvsDVIPATargetRemoved.name: ibmMvsDVIPATargetRemoved
ibmMvsDVIPATargetRemoved.description: This trap is generated by a Sysplex Distributor stack when an active target stack is removed from distribution. This can occur when a VIPADISTRIBUTE DELETE Profile statement is processed, or the target stack ends. The instance value for the ibmMvsDVIPADistConfStatus object will indicate the affected DVIPA IP address, the distributed port, and the dynamic XCF IP address of the target stack that is removed from distribution. if the ALL parameter was specified on the VIPADISTRIBUTE DELETE statement, the target stack's IP address type will be unknown (0) and its IP address will be a zero-length string.

ibmMvsDVIPATargetServerStarted.name: ibmMvsDVIPATargetServerStarted
ibmMvsDVIPATargetServerStarted.description: This trap is generated by a Sysplex Distributor stack when it receives notification from a target stack that a server has become active on a distributed port. The instance value for the ibmMvsDVIPADistPortReadyCount object will indicate the affected DVIPA IP address, the distributed port, and the target stack's dynamic XCF IP address.

ibmMvsDVIPATargetServerEnded.name: ibmMvsDVIPATargetServerEnded
ibmMvsDVIPATargetServerEnded.description: This trap is generated by a Sysplex Distributor stack when it receives notification from a target stack that a server has ended on a distributed port. The instance value for the ibmMvsDVIPADistPortReadyCount object will indicate the affected DVIPA IP address, the distributed port, and the target stack's dynamic XCF IP address.

ibmMvsTcpipSubagentColdStart.name: ibmMvsTcpipSubagentColdStart
ibmMvsTcpipSubagentColdStart.description: This trap is generated by the TCP/IP Subagent. It signifies that the Subagent, acting in a subagent role, has reinitialized itself and that its configuration may have been altered.
